H.B. 236
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Feb 26, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH10096-LG-69
Short Title: Remember 9/11 with Freedom Flag. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Moss.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT DESIGNATING THE FREEDOM FLAG AS A SYMBOL OF THE STATE'S
3 CONTINUED REMEMBRANCE OF THE LIVES LOST DUE TO THE TERRORIST
4 ATTACKS ON SEPTEMBER 11, 2001, AND AUTHORIZING THE FREEDOM FLAG
5 TO BE DISPLAYED ON SEPTEMBER 11 OF EACH YEAR.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7 SECTION 1. Chapter 145 of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
8 section to read:
9 "§ 145-32.1. 9/11 remembrance; Freedom Flag.
10 The Freedom Flag created by the Freedom Flag Foundation is designated as a symbol of the
11 State's continued remembrance of American lives lost as a result of the terrorist attacks in the
12 United States on September 11, 2001. The Freedom Flag may be flown with the flags of the
13 United States and of the State of North Carolina on public buildings and institutions and at county
14 courthouses across the State on September 11 of each year. Any named public office or public
15 official may accept a donation of one or more Freedom Flags to be displayed as provided in this
16 section."
17 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law.
*DRH10096-LG-69*

